Fudgy Brownies

8 oz bittersweet chocolate, cut into 1/4" pieces
2 tbsp cocoa powder
2 sticks (1 c) unsalted butter
1 c sugar
1 c light brown sugar, packed
1 tbsp vanilla
1 tsp kosher salt
1 tsp instant espresso powder
4 eggs
1 c ap flour
1/2 c semisweet chocolate chips
1/2 c milk chocolate chips

Preheat oven to 350F and line a 9" square pan with parchment paper. In a medium glass bowl, combine the bittersweet chocolate, cocoa powder, and butter. Set the bowl over a small saucepan of simmering water and let melt, stirring occasionally until a smooth ganache comes together. In a large mixing bowl, mix the sugars, vanilla, salt, espresso powder, and eggs until well incorporated. Once melted, stir the chocolate mixture into the bown with the sugar mixture until smooth. Fold in the flour until a batter comes together followed by the semisweet and milk chocolate chips. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake until just set, 35 min. Let cool completely, then remove from the pan and cut into 16 squares and serve.
